SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 49
By Bailey
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Randall Earl Heady of
Jackson County.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Randall Earl Heady; and
WHEREAS, the mayor of Jackson County, Mr. Heady was an exemplary public servant
and consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his
fellow citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Randall Heady was born to Willie Earl Heady and Bobbie Sue Lynn Heady
on December 29, 1963; and
WHEREAS, for twenty-eight years, Mayor Heady worked at Carwile Mechanical in
Cookeville; and
WHEREAS, he served his community as a county commissioner for eight years and was
elected mayor of Jackson County in 2018; and
WHEREAS, he led New Hope Baptist Church in Gainesboro as its pastor and had
served as a chairman on numerous committees; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Heady was also deeply devoted to his family, and he always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Heady shared more than two decades of marriage with his wife,
Joyce Ann Lee Heady, whom he married on September 8, 2001, and he was the proud father of
Chas (Rachel) Heady, Calvin Heady, Justin (Lindsay) Cochran, Amber Lou Heady, and Franny
(Robert) Hogan; and
WHEREAS, he is further survived by his siblings, Jeff (Jennifer) Heady, Karen (Kelly)
Cassetty, and Kathy (Rex) Ledbetter; and his grandchildren, Gracie Reece, Nathan Cochran,
